%N A396613 Decimal expansion of the mean distance from the center to the interior points of a regular icosahedron of unit volume.
%H A396613 <a href="/index/Ia#icosahedron">Index entries for sequences related to icosahedron</a>.
%F A396613 Equals (sqrt((5 + sqrt(5))/2)/4 - (9 + 4*sqrt(5))*Pi/180 + (23 + 9*sqrt(5))*arccosech(phi)/24)/(10*(1 + sqrt(5)/3))^(1/3), where phi is the golden ratio (A001622) (Dominik Beck, personal communication).
%e A396613 0.467285914698282339094884603179286140352476116988902...
%t A396613 RealDigits[(Sqrt[(5 + Sqrt[5])/2]/4 - (9 + 4*Sqrt[5])*Pi/180 + (23 + 9*Sqrt[5])*ArcCsch[GoldenRatio]/24)/(10*(1 + Sqrt[5]/3))^(1/3), 10, 120][[1]]
%o A396613 (PARI) (sqrt((5 + sqrt(5))/2)/4 - (9 + 4*sqrt(5))*Pi/180 + (23 + 9*sqrt(5))*asinh((sqrt(5)-1)/2)/24)/(10*(1 + sqrt(5)/3))^(1/3)
%Y A396613 Cf. A135691 (cube), A396610 (tetrahedron), A396611 (octahedron), A396612 (dodecahedron), this constant (icosahedron).
